<%- include('../partials/header') %>

<main class="container mt-5">
    <div class="row mb-4">
        <div class="col">
            <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold text-primary"><%= title %></h1>
            <p class="lead text-muted">A curated guide to the premier trekking circuits throughout the Peruvian Andes.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row align-items-center mb-5">
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <p>The Cusco region offers world-renowned trails. Here are the premier routes I highlight for incoming travelers:</p>
            
            <ul class="list-group list-group-flush mt-3">
                <li class="list-group-item ps-0">
                    <strong class="text-primary">The Classic Inca Trail:</strong> A world-famous 4-day route combining rich historical stone architecture with dense cloud forests, culminating at Machu Picchu.
                </li>
                <li class="list-group-item ps-0">
                    <strong class="text-primary">The Salkantay Trek:</strong> A rugged alpine alternative for adventure seekers, traversing high-altitude passes near massive glaciers and turquoise lagoons.
                </li>
                <li class="list-group-item ps-0">
                    <strong class="text-primary">The Ausangate Circuit:</strong> A remote trek circling a sacred peak, famous for its high-altitude landscape architecture and pristine wilderness.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="col-md-6 text-center">
            <img src="/images/resources.jpeg" alt="High altitude trekking trail" class="img-fluid rounded shadow-sm">
            <div class="mt-2 text-muted small italic">
                <p>Source: Personal guiding archive of Lourdes Soto.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</main>

<%- include('../partials/footer') %>